article_metadata.description: One of the companies that helped build the troubled federal health-care enrollment website holds a series of big-bucks contracts with Ohio state agencies. And, state officials say, CGI Group failed to deliver on one — an $11.8 million contract to develop a new software system to process vehicle titles for the Ohio Bureau of Motor Vehicles.
